If there is field that generated automatically (example: generated by default as identity),
then on this field should be annotation @GeneratedValue(strategy = SomeStrategy)

@Entity
@Table(name = "Person")
public class Peron{
    @Id
    @Column(name="id")
    @GeneratedValue(strategy=GenerationType.IDENTITY)
    private int id;
}

or with sequence:

@Entity
@Table(name = "Person")
public class Peron{
    @Id
    @Column(name="id")
    @GeneratedValue(strategy=GenerationType.SEQUENCE,
                    generator="seq_generator_person")
    @SequenceGenerator(name="seq_generator_person",
                       sequenceName="name_of_sequence_from_db",
                       allocationSize=1)
    private int id;
}

- Save
...
    Person person = new Person("Bob", 23)
    session.save(person);
    // Send requests to DB, id value for person found and written
    session.commit();
    // After that it is possible to get id value from person, which was written by DB:
    System.out.println(person.getId())
...